Installation
------------

To install this library, you can use pip:

.. code-block:: bash

    $ pip install idna

Alternatively, you can install the package using the bundled setup script:

.. code-block:: bash

    $ python setup.py install

This library works with Python 2.6 or later, and Python 3.3 or later.


Usage
-----

For typical usage, the ``encode`` and ``decode`` functions will take a
domain
name argument and perform a conversion to A-labels or U-labels
respectively.

.. code-block:: pycon

    # Python 3
    >>> import idna
    >>> idna.encode('ドメイン.テスト')
    b'xn--eckwd4c7c.xn--zckzah'
    >>> print(idna.decode('xn--eckwd4c7c.xn--zckzah'))
    ドメイン.テスト

You may use the codec encoding and decoding methods using the
``idna.codec`` module:

.. code-block:: pycon

    # Python 2
    >>> import idna.codec
    >>> print u'домена.испытание'.encode('idna')
    xn--80ahd1agd.xn--80akhbyknj4f
    >>> print 'xn--80ahd1agd.xn--80akhbyknj4f'.decode('idna')
    домена.испытание

Conversions can be applied at a per-label basis using the ``ulabel`` or
``alabel``
functions if necessary:

.. code-block:: pycon

    # Python 2
    >>> idna.alabel(u'测试')
    'xn--0zwm56d'

